JOHANNESBURG – The South African manufacturing sector has started the year on a good footing. The ABSA Purchasing Manager’s Index – which is a gauge of the sector’s health – improved by four points in January. At 49,9 points, it just misses the expansion mark of 50. Manufacturers reported the best business expectations score since 2010. READ: SA manufacturing surprises market The improvement is likely due to the stronger global growth outlook as well as better prospects for the South African economy. New sales orders also improved. eNCA